The Digital Divide in Argentina is the term used to describe the technological and connectivity gap between different demographics and regions, specifically the gaps present in the country of Argentina.
The digital divide is notable because of the widespread use of Internet, and devices used to access the Internet, in society today. In Argentina, this divide is just as prevalent as it is in most countries. With instances such as government corruption, the implementation of Internet as a core part of society, and the access to Internet not available to a lot of people effecting the digital divide in Argentina.
